column1: #FORMAT=WebAnno TSV 3.2
#T_SP=webanno.custom.Referent|entity|infstat|salience|identity
#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=Description :

#Text=Posttransplant lymphoproliferative disorder , chronic renal insufficiency , squamous cell carcinoma of the skin , anemia secondary to chronic renal insufficiency and chemotherapy , and hypertension .
#Text=The patient is here for followup visit and chemotherapy .
#Text=CHIEF COMPLAINT :
#Text=The patient is here for followup visit and chemotherapy .
#Text=DIAGNOSES :
#Text=1. Posttransplant lymphoproliferative disorder .
#Text=2. Chronic renal insufficiency .
#Text=3. Squamous cell carcinoma of the skin .
#Text=4. Anemia secondary to chronic renal insufficiency and chemotherapy .
#Text=5. Hypertension .
#Text=HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS :
#Text=A 51 - year - old white male diagnosed with PTLD in latter half of 2007 .
#Text=He presented with symptoms of increasing adenopathy , abdominal pain , weight loss , and anorexia .
#Text=He did not seek medical attention immediately .
#Text=He was finally hospitalized by the renal transplant service and underwent a lymph node biopsy in the groin , which showed diagnosis of large cell lymphoma .
#Text=He was discussed at the hematopathology conference .
#Text=Chemotherapy with rituximab plus cyclophosphamide , daunorubicin , vincristine , and prednisone was started .
#Text=First cycle of chemotherapy was complicated by sepsis despite growth factor support .
#Text=He also appeared to have become disoriented either secondary to sepsis or steroid therapy .
#Text=The patient has received 5 cycles of chemotherapy to date .
#Text=He did not keep his appointment for a PET scan after 3 cycles because he was not feeling well .
#Text=His therapy has been interrupted for infection related to squamous cell cancer , skin surgery as well as complaints of chest infection .
#Text=The patient is here for the sixth and final cycle of chemotherapy .
#Text=He states he feels well .
#Text=He denies any nausea , vomiting , cough , shortness of breath , chest pain or fatigue .
#Text=He denies any tingling or numbness in his fingers .
#Text=Review of systems is otherwise entirely negative .
#Text=Performance status on the ECOG scale is 1
#Text=PHYSICAL EXAMINATION :
#Text=VITAL SIGNS :
#Text=He is afebrile .
#Text=Blood pressure 161 / 80 , pulse 65 , weight 71.5 kg , which is essentially unchanged from his prior visit .
#Text=There is mild pallor noted .
#Text=There is no icterus , adenopathy or petechiae noted .
#Text=CHEST : Clear to auscultation .
#Text=CARDIOVASCULAR : S1 and S2 normal with regular rate and rhythm .
#Text=Systolic flow murmur is best heard in the pulmonary area .
#Text=ABDOMEN : Soft and nontender with no organomegaly .
#Text=Renal transplant is noted in the right lower quadrant with a scar present .
#Text=EXTREMITIES : Reveal no edema .
#Text=LABORATORY DATA :
#Text=CBC from today shows white count of 9.6 with a normal differential , ANC of 7400 , hemoglobin 8.9 , hematocrit 26.5 with an MCV of 109 , and platelet count of 220,000 .
#Text=ASSESSMENT AND PLAN :
#Text=1. Diffuse large B - cell lymphoma following transplantation .
#Text=The patient is to receive his sixth and final cycle of chemotherapy today .
#Text=PET scan has been ordered to be done within 2 weeks .
#Text=He will see me back for the visit in 3 weeks with CBC , CMP , and LDH .
#Text=2. Chronic renal insufficiency .
#Text=3. Anemia secondary to chronic renal failure and chemotherapy .
#Text=He is to continue on his regimen of growth factor support .
#Text=4. Hypertension .
#Text=This is elevated today because he held his meds because he is getting rituximab other than that this is well controlled .
#Text=His CMP is pending from today .
#Text=5. Squamous cell carcinoma of the skin .
#Text=The scalp is well healed .
#Text=He still has an open wound on the right posterior aspect of his trunk .
#Text=This has no active drainage , but it is yet to heal .
#Text=This probably will heal by secondary intention once chemotherapy is finished .
#Text=Prescription for prednisone as part of his chemotherapy has been given to him .
